{{Year in Sri Lanka|1991}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1991]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[Ranasinghe Premadasa]]

==Events==
* The [[First Battle of Elephant Pass]] took place on July 1991 for the purpose of controlling the Sri Lankan military base of [[Elephant Pass]], which was of strategic importance as it was attached to the northern mainland known as [[Wanni]] with the [[Jaffna Peninsula]].<ref name='atimes'>[http://atimes.com/atimes/South_Asia/DG27Df02.html Asia Times]</ref>
* The UNP Minister of Defense, [[Ranjan Wijeratne]], is killed in a car bomb. The [[LTTE]] is supposedly responsible for it.<ref>{{Cite news|title=On This Day 2 March - 1991: Sri Lankan hardliner among 19 killed in blast|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/march/2/newsid_4201000/4201675.stm|publisher=[[BBC]] |date=2 March 1991|accessdate=17 June 2011}}</ref>

