[[Image:Wasserturm 1.jpg|thumb|250px|Ahlen water tower]]
The '''Ahlen water tower''' is an [[Industry|industrial]] [[monument]] and [[landmark]] in the [[Ahlen]], [[Germany]].
The [[spherical]] [[water tank]] is {{convert|44|m}} high and has a capacity of {{convert|1000|m3}}. From 1915 to 1917, the water tower served as the sole water supply for the [[Westphalia]] [[Mining|mine]] and the miners colony built in 1892 by Gelsenwasser AG.<ref name=triposo>{{cite web|title=Ahlen Water Tower|url=http://www.triposo.com/poi/Ahlen_Water_Tower|publisher=triposo.com|accessdate=9 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=placeknow>{{cite web|title=Ahlen Water Tower|url=http://placeknow.com/attractions/germany/ahlen/ahlen-water-tower-13370|publisher=placeknow.com|accessdate=3 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=virtualglobetrotting>{{cite web|title=Water Tower Ahlen|url=http://virtualglobetrotting.com/map/abandoned-coal-mine-2/view/?service=0|publisher=virtualglobetrotting.com|accessdate=9 February 2014}}</ref>
Today the distinctive blue water tower is monument and is a historical example of the early development of [[riveting]] at the beginning of the 20th century.
